14, Leeds United retired the number 17 shirt due to then-owner [[Massimo Cellino]]'s superstitious beliefs. Up until June 2014, the last occupant of the shirt had been [[Michael Brown (footballer, born 1977)|Michael Brown]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.itv.com/news/calendar/2014-05-15/not-for-tv-cellinos-best-bits/ |title=Massimo Cellino says Leeds \"has no manager\" |date=15 May 2014 |work=ITV |access-date=15 May 2014}}</ref> The shirt was brought out of retirement on 3 July 2019, when Leeds new signing of [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] international [[H\u00e9lder Costa (footballer)|H\u00e9lder Costa]] was given the number.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/25119/leeds-united-complete-helder-costa-signing |title=LEEDS UNITED COMPLETE HELDER COSTA SIGNING |date=3 July 2019 |website=Leeds United Official Site |access-date=3 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Notable players===\n{{Main|List of Leeds United F.C. players}}\n\n==First-team staff==\n{{see also|List of Leeds United F.C. managers}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n[[File:Marcelo Bielsa OM 2015.jpg|thumbnail|upright|[[Argentine]] Manager [[Marcelo Bielsa]], Leeds United's current head coach]]\n|-\n!Position\n!Staff\n|-\n|Head Coach|| {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Marcelo Bielsa]]<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/23433/marcelo-bielsa-named-head-coach |title=Marcelo Bielsa Named Head Coach |date=15 June 2018 |work=Leeds United F.C. |access-date=15 June 2018}}</ref> \n|-\n|Assistant Head Coach||{{flagicon|ARG}} Pablo Quiroga<ref name=\"firstteamstaff\">{{cite news |url=https://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/full-list-of-leeds-united-head-coach-marcelo-bielsa-s-backroom-staff-at-elland-road-1-9304933 |title=Full list of Leeds United head coach Marcelo Bielsa's backroom staff at Elland Road |newspaper=Yorkshire Evening Post |access-date=16 August 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|Assistant Head Coach||{{flagicon|CHI}} Diego Reyes<ref name=firstteamstaff